main event: A circular object was detected by radar close to the ground in Glen Spry, New York on June 27, 1961. The object flashed on and off the radar scope and was estimated to be moving at 700 mph.
interesting points: The object was only detected on radar, with no visual sightings reported.
The radar operators concluded the detection could have been due to a malfunction or interference, as no other details were available.
The object was described as a single circular object that moved close to the ground.
The report does not provide any information on the size or appearance of the object beyond it being circular.
The sighting lasted for approximately 5 minutes.
